Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:

1. illustrate the basic principles of oligonucleotides and proteins as therapeutics, including their research, production, stability, administration, and functions;
2. comment on the principles of immunology in pharmaceutical science, and the use of cell therapies, antibodies and cytokines for the diagnosis and treatment of diseases;
3. use simple bioinformatics tools to conduct basic analysis;
4. illustrate the principles of pharmacogenomics, apply pharmacogenomics tools to set and adjust dosage regimens, and to render decisions on applications of drug products.

