courses.course_syllabus:
The course provides a comprehensive overview of the drug development process. Upon completion of the course, students should be able to acquire a general understanding of the interrelated activities throughout the drug development cycle. A series of topics are included to enable students to understand the various steps in developing a drug from discovery to commercialization.

List of topics:

(i) General overview;

(ii) Drug design;

(iii) Drug delivery systems;

(iv) Pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics;

(v) Metabolism;

(vi) Toxicity and drug safety;

(viii) Clinical trials;

(ix) Pharmacoeconomics;

(x) Regulatory issues
